  "prompt": "What is the meaning of tax rebate? As per the year budget, tax rebate is now 5000 for salary more than 5 lakh. What does it mean in a lay man language?",
  "response": "A tax rebate is essentially a refund or reduction in the amount of tax you owe to the government. It can be thought of as a benefit that reduces your taxable income or the total tax amount you have to pay.\n\nIn the context you provided, if the tax rebate is set at \u20b95,000 for individuals earning a salary of more than \u20b95 lakh, it means that if you earn more than \u20b95 lakh, you can effectively reduce your tax liability by \u20b95,000. \n\nIn simpler terms:\n\n- If your income is above \u20b95 lakh, you could potentially have a tax bill that is lower by \u20b95,000 because of this rebate.\n- So, for example, if your total tax due on your income was \u20b930,000, after applying the rebate, you would only need to pay \u20b925,000.\n\nThis measure aims to provide some relief to taxpayers by reducing the overall amount they need to pay in taxes.",
